VW is the most popular car brand among South African techies, according to the MyBroadband 2017 Motoring Survey. The survey was completed by 1,356 tech-savvy readers, many of whom work in the ICT industry. 91.89% of respondents owned a car, with 72.42% driving a petrol-powered vehicle. Ford and Toyota came in second and third respectively in terms of popularity – both at just over 10% of the vote. The majority of respondents said their household owned two cars. One-car households came in second place, while 5.78% of respondents said their household owned four cars. The infographic below details the results of the survey. 